args: Durant, your wounds are not yet healed!\nPlease, just take your mediâ€”
Shut up. I don't take orders from you.
How are you liking life here?
Eh, it ain't bad. Once you swear to join me,\nI wouldn't mind movin' HQ out here.
I thought I made my answer quite clear.
Oh, you did. But why else would I be\nstickin' around? Ya better not be thinkin'\nwe're pals or somethin'.
It's fine, Elly. I think this is just Durant\nbeing Durant.
The hell's that supposed to mean?!
Talkin' like you know me and junk...
I've met a lotta punks in my life,\nbut NOBODY has ticked me off\nthe way you do.
I bring a report, Your Majesty.
A man is at the gate saying he wishes\nto join your cause.
I see. Okay, I'll meet with him.
Understood. I will bring him here.
New blood, huh?\nThis should be interesting.
I'll tag along as well. Wanna see how good\nya really are at judgin' character.
I have brought the visitor, Your Majesty.
My name is Dan, and it's truly a pleasure\nto meet you.
Hello, Dan. I'm told you'd like to\njoin us?
That's right. My village was destroyed\nby the Empire overnight.
They are a blight on this land, and I'm\ntired of feeling powerless to stop them!
So when I heard what you've been doing\nhere, I was convinced joining you would\nhelp me make a difference.
I'm an accomplished martial artist;\nI have no doubt I can be of use.
So, please: Will you let me join\nyour cause?
Of course. Welcome to the fold, Dan.
Oh, thank you! I will make myself useful,\nI swear it.
I shall prepare a room for you.\nThis way, please.
...You're an idiot. What could you possibly\ntell about a guy from a conversation like\nthat? He didn't tell you squat.
Think about it this way: How do you know\nhe's not an assassin?
If he is, your comrades could be in danger\nnow too.

...I see what you're saying. On the other
hand, though, I wouldn't feel right
defaulting to doubt anytime I meet
someone new.
I wanted to believe in him. If he ends up\nbetraying me, I'll deal with that pain when\nit happens.
Everyone in the Halidom trusts His\nMajesty's judgment. When we are\nhurt, we are hurt together.

You all love to talk pretty, huh?
What a load of rubbish.
Don't blame me if you end up dead in a
ditch somewhere.
The hell? Why would I be concerned?!
Oh yeah? You ready to fall in line then?
I'm not talking about one of us working\nfor the otherâ€”I'm talking about the\nconnection we share.
If you're not in my pack, you're no comrade\nof mine. I'm outta here.
Goodness... He certainly knows how\nto bark, that one.
Yeah, but he's not a bad guy.\nHe'll come around.
So you're Dan now, are ya?
I see you're still doin' the wet work.
...You mangy dog. Musta been some real\ntasty grub here to get you to heel, eh?
You'd know. Now cut the crapâ€”you're here\nto kill prince, ain't ya? Empire put ya\nup to it?
Maybe. If the pay's right, I'll kill anyone.\nEven you, if you get in my way.
Heh. I don't stick my neck out for strangers.
Oh? Prince not ï¼‚pack materialï¼‚ then?
Look, I got my reasons for bein' here,\nand you got yours.
Heh. Right. Then I guess you won't go\ngettin' in my way, yeah?
Look, {player_name}.  This world\nain't all sunshine and rainbows.
Some day soon, you're gonna have to get\ndown in the muck with the rest of us.
